List of used libraries:

libonion		(webserver; no debian package available, see Makefile target 'onion' for compiling)
OpenCV >= 2.3	(image analyse)
libfreenect (kinect driver)
libboost (for signal functionality)
oscpack (OSC implementation)
libjpeg8 or libpng
cmake

=======

== Debian/Ubuntu ==
List of packages (not minimal)

sudo apt-get install \
libfreenect-dev \
liblo-dev libboost-regex-dev libboost-system-dev \
libpng-dev libjpeg-turbo8-dev \
libopencv-core-dev libopencv-imgproc-dev libopencv-highgui-dev


== Arch/Manjaro ==

Installing packages e.g. by

	sudo pacman -S opencv boost boost-libs
	git clone --depth=1 https://aur.archlinux.org/libfreenect.git \
	&& cd libfreenect && echo "Disable python dependencies in PKGBUILD" \
	&& git apply ./3rdparty/libfreenect_without_python.patch \
	&& makepkg -i
